data.content:
## What Changed

`Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi` 10.0 pulls in **Microsoft.OpenApi v2.0**, which targets OpenAPI 3.1 and has several breaking model changes:

| .NET 9 (OpenApi v1.x) | .NET 10 (OpenApi v2.x) |
|---|---|
| `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any.OpenApiString` etc. | Removed – use `System.Text.Json.Nodes.JsonNode` |
| `schema.Nullable` (bool) | Removed – nullability is a type flag (`JsonSchemaType.Null`) |
| `OpenApiSecurityRequirement` inherits `Dictionary<…>` | Now a class with a `Schemes` property |
| `ReferenceType.SecurityScheme` enum | `ReferenceType.SecurityScheme` (still exists, but verify import) |

## Fixed Code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;          // ← replaces Microsoft.OpenApi.Any
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        // OpenApiString → JsonValue
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
    }

    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecurityScheme
    {
        Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }
    };
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        // No longer a dictionary itself; populate via Schemes property
        new OpenApiSecurityRequirement
        {
            Schemes = { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
        }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
            {
                // Nullable property is gone in OpenAPI 3.1.
                // Remove Null from the type flags instead:
                property.Value.Type = property.Value.Type & ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
            }
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

## Summary of Fixes

1. **`new OpenApiString("1.0")`** → `JsonValue.Create("1.0")` (add `using System.Text.Json.Nodes;`)
2. **`property.Value.Nullable = false`** → clear the `Null` flag: `property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null`
3. **`new() { [scheme] = scopes }`** → `new OpenApiSecurityRequirement { Schemes = { [scheme] = scopes } }`
4. Remove `using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;` (namespace no longer exists).
